a parameter is declared in the parentheses after the function name.
parameters are initialised using arguments during a function call. they cannot be left uninitialised.
the parameter name is visible throughout the function block. the object associated with the name exists throughout the
execution of the function.

a local variable is declared in a block.
variables may be initialised with initialisers. uninitialised local variables are default initialised.
the variable name is visible throughout the block in which it was initialised. the object associated with the name
exists throughout the execution of the block.

a local static variable is declared in a block.
variables may be initialised with initialisers. uninitialised local static variables are value initialised.
the variable name is visible throughout the block in which it was initialised. the object associated with the name
exists throughout the execution of the program.
